'''Compartmentalized ciliogenesis''' is the most common type of [[ciliogenesis]] where the [[cilium]] [[axoneme]] is formed separated from the cytoplasm by the ciliary membrane and a ciliary gate known as the transition zone.<ref>Shared and Distinct Mechanisms of Compartmentalized and Cytosolic Ciliogenesis. Avidor-Reiss T, Leroux MR. Curr Biol. 2015 Dec 7;25(23):R1143-50. doi: 10.1016/j.cub.2015.11.001. http://0-resolver.ebscohost.com.carlson.utoledo.edu/openurl?sid=Entrez%3aPubMed&id=pmid%3a26654377&site=ftf-live</ref>
