=== Rankings and reputation === {{Infobox world university ranking|THE_Under50=151-200|THE_Under50_ref=('18)<ref name="timeshighereducation.com">[https://www.timeshighereducation.com/world-university-rankings/sao-paulo-state-university-unesp]</ref>|THE_Emerging=161|THE_Emerging_ref=('18)<ref>[https://www.timeshighereducation.com/world-university-rankings/2018/emerging-economies-university-rankings#!/page/0/length/25/name/S%C3%A3o%20Paulo%20State/sort_by/rank/sort_order/asc/cols/stats]</ref>|THE_Brazil=4|THE_Brazil_ref=<ref>[https://www.timeshighereducation.com/student/best-universities/best-universities-brazil]</ref>|THE_LA=11|THE_LA_ref=('18)<ref>[https://www.timeshighereducation.com/world-university-rankings/2018/latin-america-university-rankings#!/page/0/length/25/sort_by/rank/sort_order/asc/cols/undefined]</ref>|QS_LA=10|QS_LA_ref=('18)<ref>[https://www.topuniversities.com/university-rankings/latin-american-university-rankings/2018]</ref>|ARWU_W=301-400|ARWU_W_ref=('18)<ref>[http://www.shanghairanking.com/World-University-Rankings/UNESP.html]</ref>|QS_W=491-500|QS_W_ref=('18)<ref>[https://www.topuniversities.com/universities/unesp]</ref>|THE_W=601-800|THE_W_ref=('18)<ref name="timeshighereducation.com">[https://www.timeshighereducation.com/world-university-rankings/sao-paulo-state-university-unesp]</ref>}} In 2012, UNESP ranked second among public universities in the "VIII Best Universities Award", annually presented by the student publication guide, Editora Abril.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://guiadoestudante.abril.com.br/universidades/guia-do-estudante-divulga-as-melhores-universidades-do-brasil-em-2012/|title=GE divulga as melhores universidades do Brasil em 2012|work=Guia do Estudante|access-date=2018-08-09|language=pt-BR}}</ref>
In 2013, the UK publication Times Higher Education (THE) pointed to UNESP, alongside Unicamp, as one of the World's Top 100 "Young" Universities (under 50 years old)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.timeshighereducation.com/Journals/THE/THE/31_May_2012/attachments/THE_100_Under_50_.pdf|title=The Top 100 Universities under 50|last=|first=|date=|website=Times Higher Education|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref> and as the 11th best university in emerging countries.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://epoca.globo.com/vida/noticia/2013/12/brasil-tem-b4-universidadesb-entre-melhores-dos-paises-emergentes.html|title=Brasil tem 4 universidades entre as melhores dos países emergentes|work=revistaepoca.globo.com|access-date=2018-08-09|language=pt-br}}</ref>
QS World University Rankings ranked the University of São Paulo as the 9th best in Latin America (2014),<ref name=":0">{{Cite news|url=https://www.topuniversities.com/universities/unesp#wurs|title=UNESP|date=2015-07-16|work=Top Universities|access-date=2018-08-09}}</ref> the 34th best in BRICS,<ref name=":0" /> the 4th best in Brazil, and within the 491-500th best universities worldwide in 2018.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.topuniversities.com/university-rankings/world-university-rankings/2018|title=QS World University Rankings 2018|date=2017-02-01|work=Top Universities|access-date=2018-08-09}}</ref>
The Academic Classification of World Universities (ARWU) of 2017 ranked UNESP in the 301st-400th group of the best universities in the world and as the third best institution of higher education in Brazil.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.shanghairanking.com/ARWU2017.html|title=ARWU World University Rankings 2017 {{!}} Academic Ranking of World Universities 2017 {{!}} Top 500 universities {{!}} Shanghai Ranking - 2017|website=www.shanghairanking.com|access-date=2018-08-09}}</ref>
The institution was also ranked as the 8th best university in Latin America, the 4th in Brazil and the 408th in the world by the Webometrics Ranking of World Universities in 2017.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.webometrics.info/en/Americas/Latin_America|title=Latin America {{!}} Ranking Web of Universities|website=www.webometrics.info|access-date=2018-08-09}}</ref>
UNESP ranked in the 151-200th group of the Young University Rankings 2018 and in the 601-800th group of the World University Rankings 2018 by THE.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.timeshighereducation.com/world-university-rankings/sao-paulo-state-university-unesp|title=São Paulo State University (UNESP)|website=Times Higher Education (THE)|access-date=2018-08-15}}</ref>
== Research == {{Expand section|date=August 2018}} Research an UNESP is centrally organized by the Research Vice-President's office (PROPe).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www2.unesp.br/portal#!/international/research|title=Unesp - Universidade Estadual Paulista - Portal|website=www2.unesp.br|access-date=2018-08-15}}</ref> The university currently has its main research focus in the areas of [[Bioenergy]], [[Biotechnology]], [[Climate change|Climate Change]], [[Nanotechnology]], [[Pharmacology|Pharmaceutical Development and Technology]], [[Pre-clinical development|Pre-Clinical]] and [[Drug development|Clinical development]], [[Public policy|Public Policy]], Sea Sciences and [[Stem-cell research|Stem Cell]] research.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www2.unesp.br/portal#!/international/research/strategic-areas|title=Unesp - Universidade Estadual Paulista - Portal|website=www2.unesp.br|access-date=2018-08-15}}</ref>
In 2010, [[UNESCO]], an agency of the [[United Nations]] (UN), named UNESP as the 2nd university in Brazil in numbers of scientific articles of international level, being responsible for 8% of the national scientific production, alongside [[Unicamp|UNICAMP]] and second to [[University of São Paulo|USP.]] <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.planetauniversitario.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=18421:unesco-aponta-unesp-em-segundo-lugar-no-brasil-em-producao-cientifica&catid=27:notas-do-campus&Itemid=73|title=Unesco aponta Unesp em segundo lugar no Brasil em produção científica|website=www.planetauniversitario.com|language=pt-br|access-date=2018-08-09}}</ref> Other sources state that UNESP is accounting for 25% of total high-quality scientific publications in Brazil.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.omicsonline.org/universities/Sao_Paulo_State_University/|title=Sao Paulo State University|website=www.omicsonline.org|access-date=2018-08-15}}</ref>
